ice, sitting in the back seat of a car or taxi beside a window. She now wears a beige trench coat and holds the Model 100 on a small wooden surface in front of her. City scenery outside the car window passes by in soft blur. She looks down, positions the computer in front of her, and begins using it, resting one hand near the keyboard and the other near the side of the machine. Her posture is focused and businesslike, using the computer as a traveling workstation.\n\nThe setting changes again to a home-like room with warm wood tones. A sofa sits in the background, with a side table holding a cream-colored telephone. A coffee table is cluttered with papers, a cup, and small objects. The same dark-haired person, likely Fletcher, sits forward over the Model 100 on the coffee table, typing and working intently. The room includes a lamp and dark furniture in the background, giving the sense of a comfortable living room being used as an office.\n\nA close view shows hands typing rapidly on the Model 100’s black keys. The long display screen shows faint lines of text, though the words are not readable. A pair of eyeglasses and papers lie above the computer on the table. The hands continue working across the keyboard, demonstrating it as a word processor or general work machine. Then an arm wearing a wristwatch reaches past the computer toward telephone equipment. Beside the computer are cords, a black acoustic coupler-like device, and a cream push-button telephone. A white handset is lifted and placed into the black cradle, with cords running between the phone equipment and the workspace, visually suggesting the portable computer connecting through the telephone line.\n\nBack in the office, the older man returns through the doorway. He is now without his suit jacket, wearing a dark vest over his dress shirt and tie, and carrying papers. He steps into the office where the printer and CRT terminal sit on the table against the yellow wall. Papers are scattered on the desk, an